OL,3,CWhat is Labour's huge shake-up of
OL,4,Clocal government all about?
OL,6,FBut since the policy was first
OL,7,Fintroduced, many are pushing to have
OL,8,Fcouncils representing much smaller
OL,9,Fareas. And government sources have
OL,10,Ftold me that they are open to that
OL,11,F(suggesting the current average size
OL,12,Fof a unitary is 270,000).
OL,14,FWhat would happen then? The report
OL,15,Fclaims that replacing the two-tier
OL,16,Fsystem with 58 new unitaries
OL,17,F(representing populations of around
OL,18,F300,000) would actually cost taxpayers
OL,19,Fmoney, to the tune of #850m in five
OL,20,Fyears.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
